You are Codex. Build a production-ready, original-design SaaS web app that combines:

(A) A best-in-class legal practice management system (Clio/PracticePanther/MyCase/Filevine-class parity in core objects and flexibility)
(B) A legal AI “case workforce” (Eve-like AI workflows across intake → pleadings → discovery → settlement)
...tailored specifically for HOME IMPROVEMENT / RESIDENTIAL CONSTRUCTION LITIGATION, but works for any type of law.

ABSOLUTE CONSTRAINTS (IP + Ethics + Safety)
- AI outputs are drafts only; require “Attorney Review” and record provenance (prompt, sources, model, timestamp, user).
- Security-first multi-tenant SaaS with strict isolation; RBAC/ABAC; audit logs; encryption; secure uploads.

PORTABILITY & MIGRATION (HARD REQUIREMENT)
This product must make it easy to migrate IN and OUT, comparable to top systems.

1) Canonical Data Model + External IDs
- Every core entity must support:
  - stable UUID primary key
  - external references: {source_system, external_id, external_parent_id, imported_at, import_batch_id}
  - raw_source_payload JSON (optional) for audit and re-mapping
- Build a generic Import Framework:
  - ImportBatch (status, source_system, started_by, mapping_profile_id)
  - ImportItem (entity_type, row_number, raw_json, resolved_entity_id, errors, warnings)
  - MappingProfile: field mapping rules, transforms, dedupe rules, conflict rules
  - ConflictRuleProfile: reusable advanced conflict logic (match weights, relationship proximity, matter-status filters, escalation rules)
  - Dedupe engine using: email/phone/name + fuzzy match + user-confirm merge UI

2) Data Sources to Support
Implement importers/connectors in a plugin architecture:

MVP Importers (must be working end-to-end):
- “MyCase Full Backup Import”: accept ZIP containing multiple CSVs; map contacts/companies, cases/matters, tasks, calendar events, invoices/payments, time entries, notes/messages where possible.
- “Clio Migration Template Import”: accept CSV/XLSX in expected template-like format; map contacts, matters, tasks, calendar, activities/time entries, notes, phone logs/emails where available.
- “Generic CSV Import”: user chooses entity type, maps columns, previews, imports.

Phase 2 (structure now, can stub actual authentication):
- API Connectors (OAuth where applicable) for:
  - Clio Manage API connector
  - MyCase API connector
  - Filevine API connector
  - PracticePanther API connector (or generic REST connector)
- Each connector must support incremental sync + webhooks subscription (where available) with idempotency keys.

3) Export / “Exit Strategy”
- Full Backup export: a ZIP containing:
  - CSVs per entity type (contacts, matters, tasks, events, time, invoices, payments, messages, notes, custom fields)
  - Documents in folder structure with a manifest.json linking docs to records
- Provide a “Data Dictionary” page that explains exported files.
- Provide import/export test fixtures + automated tests verifying round-trip integrity.

TARGET USERS / ROLES
- Multi-tenant Organization (firm) with isolated data
- Roles: Admin, Attorney, Paralegal, Intake Specialist, Billing/Accounting, Client (portal-only), “Vendor/Expert” (optional limited portal)
- Matter-level ethical wall: matters can be restricted to a team; also allow “deny list” users.

TECH STACK (choose and implement fully)
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind (or similar), responsive
- Backend: Next.js API routes OR NestJS (TypeScript) separate service (choose and stick to it)
- DB: Postgres + Prisma
- Vector: pgvector
